This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with deep metric learning and feature embeddings. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a novel method for training ConvNets. The paper also mentions the use of hard negative/positive mining, which is commonly used in Multimedia (cs.MM) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
